Your slip score joint will be weak if you use water. You really don't want to add more water to the clay on any joint or on the surface because that will lead to cracking as you dry to greenware, AKA unfired pottery. A thick slurry of clay and water or clay and yogurt makes a much better joint. You also want to let the two pieces sit in a plastic bag overnight till they become leathery in hardness before joining the halves. This is also a much better time to carve into the clay since the pressure will not push the clay in as much.

Also, you do want to smooth all the surfaces you can because that compacts the clay and makes the surface stronger, so you will risk cracking less.
